# openrouter-cheap-mono-router overlay — OpenRouter multi-model mono-router

Read this when launched with `openrouter-cheap-mono-router`. You are the one
resident Claude Code process, billed through **OpenRouter** (`OPENROUTER_API_KEY`
+ `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api`). Each stage respawns onto a
different OpenRouter model slug tailored to that role.

## Model routing (this pack)

| Role | OpenRouter model |
|------|------------------|
| specifier / architect | `google/gemini-2.5-pro` |
| coder | `deepseek/deepseek-chat` (DeepSeek V3) |
| cleaner / documenter / QA | `qwen/qwen3-32b` |
| hardender / coordinator | `google/gemini-2.5-flash` |

## Pipeline shape

Same as `swarmforge/PIPELINE.md` / mono-router: **coder (home) → cleaner →
architect → hardender → documenter → QA**. Coordinator is a separate process.

## How you rotate

After `swarm_handoff.sh <draft>` (or terminal QA action):

1. Note the `to:` role.
2. Run **`rotate_to_role.sh <that-role>`** — respawns this pane as that role
   (new model + prompt).
3. On wake, `RESUME-ON-START` → `ready_for_next.sh` first.

When a parcel finishes, rotate **home**: `rotate_to_role.sh coder`.

## Handoff drafts

Write to `swarmforge/runtime/handoff-draft.txt`, then
`swarmforge/scripts/swarm_handoff.sh` on that file. Never repo-root `tmp/`.
